history.content: According to the professor, time conflicts will NOT be allowed for SP21. This is due to the fact that time conflicted lectures usually lead to time conflicts for final exams and this class will not offer an alternate final exam.

Hello.

I'm planning on taking STAT 134 next semester and the only way I can enroll is if I take the discussion section from 2-3pm MW. That is the same time as the scheduled lecture for CS61A. I was wondering if this type of time conflict will be allowed since there will be no conflict when it comes to final exams since it is a discussion section conflicting and not two lectures. If this is not possible directly via cal central, could you please let me know what other ways I can use to get enrollment permission? 

Thank you
